sy him lof symle
þurh woruld worulda,
and wuldres blæd,
ar and on-wald,
in þam uplican
rodea rice!
he is on ryht cyning
middan-geardes,
and mæge þrymmes,
wuldre biwund,
in þær wlitegan byrig;
hafað us alyfed
 luko auctor,
þæt we motun her
merueri,
god-dædum begietan
gaudia in celo,
þær we motun
maxima regna
secan, and gesittan
sedibus alis,
lifgan in lisse
luko et pacis,
agan eardinga
alma lætitiæ,
brucan blæd daga
blandem et mitem,
geseon sigora frean
sine fine,
and him lof singan
laude peenne,
eadg mid englum,
